descript.abstract: This feature class represents the wildland fire protection areas within Alaska. The State of Alaska, Department of Natural Resources (DNR), Bureau of Land Management, Alaska Fire Service, and the US Forest Service have responsibility for providing and coordinating wildland fire suppression services. Geographic units where the State of Alaska, Department of Natural Resources is is protecting agency are called "Areas", the AFS units are "Zones", and the USFS units are "Forests".
descript.purpose: This feature class represents the wildland fire protection areas within Alaska.

No formal logical accuracy tests were conducted.

prcStep.stepDesc: Edited polygons to reflect changes in the AFS Military Zone. The JBER (Anchorage area) from AFS Military Zone and added to DNR Anchorage/Mat-Su area.
Edited Southwest Area by merging the two 'mainland' polygons into a single polygon.
Edited the boundary between Tanana Zone and Upper Yukon Zone. The Dalton Highway was used to split the Zones.
